Terminalia
. Hypopygium black; epandrium triangular in dorsal view, with small invagination apically (
Fig. 2c
); gonocoxites ovoid, fused medially narrowly, apicomesal process as long as gonostylus, with small bristles; gonostylus oval, apically curved, pointed (
Figs. 2b, c
); basal aedeagal process narrow in dorsal view with two lateral rami basally, lateral aedeagal apodemes narrow (
Fig. 2a
); aedeagus apically curved (
Fig. 2d
).
